    "body": "I wanted to try implementing c11-std-atomics into cython since free-threading is going to become extremely common in the future and users likewise should have some way of easily access to atomic apis in C and not just in C++. \r\n\r\nMy other suggestion or workaround would be to make a header file similar to pyatomics but for Cython that could have unified support for gcc, msvc intrinsics, and std.\r\n\r\n> [!WARNING]\r\n> I have no idea if fused templating is going to work or not but it was worth a shot so for now this pr is a draft.\r\n",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "_links": {
